21
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:10,583
The reentrancy pattern: the attacker calls withdraw on the victim contract.

22
00:02:10,683 --> 00:02:16,531
The victim sends ETH to the attacker's contract. The attacker's receive

23
00:02:16,631 --> 00:02:22,227
function calls withdraw again — before the first call completes. The

24
00:02:22,327 --> 00:02:27,338
victim hasn't updated its balance yet, so it sends ETH again.

25
00:02:27,438 --> 00:02:34,542
Repeat until the pool is drained. The fix: Checks-Effects-Interactions pattern. Update

26
00:02:34,642 --> 00:02:38,983
all state — set balance to zero — before any external

27
00:02:39,083 --> 00:02:44,596
call. Or use a nonReentrant mutex lock. Modern best practice: both.

28
00:02:44,666 --> 00:02:49,730
